<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>

    <%- include('../common/header.ejs', {Document: "Update Article" }) %>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style/addArticle.css">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style/updateArticle.css">
        <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/froala-editor@latest/css/froala_editor.pkgd.min.css" rel="stylesheet"
            type="text/css" />
            <link href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Charmonman' rel='stylesheet'>
            <link href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Cinzel Decorative' rel='stylesheet'>

</head>


<body>
    <%- include('../common/navbar.ejs') %>

        <section class="d-flex justify-content-center sectionArticle">

            <div class="col-9 border-right border-dark h-100">
    
                <form action="/articles/setup" method="patch" enctype="multipart/form-data" class="" id="formAddArticle">
    
                    <section class="col-12 d-flex justify-content-center p-3 mb-4 border-bottom border-dark">
    
                        <div class="col-3 border p-2 m-2 " id="imageContainer">
                            <div class="overChoose">
                                <i class='far fa-edit' style='font-size:20px'></i> <span class='choose'> Choose image </span>
                            </div>
                            <img src="/images/article/<%= data.image  %> " class="img-fluid col-12" style="max-height:400px;"
                            alt="Responsive image" id="imageArticle">
                        </div>
    
                        <div class="col-9 p-2 m-2">
                            <input type="file" name="articlePicture" id="formFile"
                                class=" form-control col-12 col-md-12 m-0 mb-1 d-none " required>
    
                            <p class="text-success head col-12 m-1 p-2 ps-0 ms-0">TITLE</p>
                            <input type="text" name="title" class="col-12 col-md-12 m-0 mb-1" required value="<%= data.title %>">
    
                            <p class="text-success head col-12 m-1 p-2 ps-0 ms-0">DESCRIPTION</p>
                            <input type="text" name="description" class="col-12 m-0 mb-3" required value="<%= data.description %>">
    
                        </div>
    
                    </section>
    
                    <div>
    
                        <textarea id="mytextarea" name="content">
                            <%= data.content %> 
                    </textarea required>
    
                    <input type="text" data-articleid="<%= data._id %>" value="" class="d-none" name="id" id="idInput">

                    <input class="button-37 mt-5" value="update article" id="updateArticleSubmit">
    
                </div>
    
            </form>
    
        </div>
    
        <div>
            <div class="p-5  align-items-flex-start">
    
                <button id="commentShow" class="commentBtnShow col-12">Comments</button>
    
                <br><br><br>
    
    
                <div class="p-3">
                    <h4 style="font-family: 'Charmonman';">
                        About Articles
                    </h4>
    
                    <hr>
                    <p class="text-justify" style="color: rgb(12, 71, 19);">
                        In the 11th century, a Japanese woman known as Murasaki Shikibu wrote “The Tale of Genji,” a 54-chapter story of courtly seduction believed to be the world’s first novel.

                        Over 1,000 years later, people the world over are still engrossed by novels — even in an era where stories appear on handheld screens and disappear 24 hours later.
                        
                        What exactly do human beings get from reading books? Is it just a matter of pleasure, or are there benefits beyond enjoyment? The scientific answer is a resounding “yes.”
                        
                        Reading books benefits both your physical and mental health, and those benefits can last a lifetime. They begin in early childhood and continue through the senior years. Here’s a brief explanation of how reading books can change your brain — and your body — for the better.
                    </p>
    
                </div>
    
                <br><br><br>
    
                <div class="p-3">
                    <h4 style="font-family: 'Charmonman';">
                        About Author
                    </h4>
    
                    <hr>
                    <p class="text-justify" style="color: rgb(12, 71, 19);">
                        The essential characteristics of a good writer are that you need lots of patience to keep the words flowing from your mind.

                        Your mind should have the clarity to keep your choice of words at its best.
                        
                        The best part of being a writer is that you get loyal fans for your writing pieces if your ebook or paper version book becomes popular.
                        
                        These fans keep purchasing your books, which is the best reward a writer can have.
                        
                        It would be best if you were reading a lot to enrich your vocabulary to not sound like a newbie writer when people read your content.
                        
                        One of the most delicate characteristics of a good writer is to stay neutral with your views.
                        
                        Our views judge what kind of a writer we are, so we should have positivity around us.
                        
                        Never look back once we decide on something. We can have amendments, but should not change our decision.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
    
        </section>


        
        <div class="toast" style="position: absolute; top: 20px; right: 20px;">
            <div class="toast-header">
                <strong class="mr-auto">Message</strong>
                <button id="toastBtn" type="button" class="ml-2 mb-1 close" data-dismiss="toast" aria-label="Close">
                    <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
                </button>
            </div>
            <div class="toast-body">
            </div>
        </div>


        
        <%- include('../common/scripts.ejs') %>
            <script src="/script/updateArticle.js"></script>
            <script type="text/javascript"
                src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/froala-editor@latest/js/froala_editor.pkgd.min.js"></script>

            <script>
                new FroalaEditor('textarea');
            </script>
</body>

</html>